e\" to 10mb and click save.\r\n* logout the admin user.\r\n* have a look at .htaccess: it now says \"php_value upload_max_filesize 10m\"\r\n* log back into owncloud with your admin account.\r\n* go to the admin page\r\n* look at the displayed value of the \"maximum upload size\". in my installation\r\n  it now says \"32 mb\" again.\r\n* (info: the global upload limit in the php.ini is 32m in this installation.)\r\n\r\ninstallation info:\r\nowncloud 5.0.8\r\nsqlite\r\nphp 5.3.26 as fastcgi\r\napache webserver on shared hosting (linux)\r\n","closed_by":null}